    task ws_withdraw_proposal_message "Withdraw-proposal message: client → server (proposer-only authority, emits entity-removed events)" {
      effort 0.5d
      allocate team
      complete 100
      depends !ws_propose_message, !ws_message_envelope
      note -8<-
        Source of debt: tasks/refinements/moderator-ui/mod_proposed_entity_canvas_visibility.md D4 + D7 — the `entity-removed` event kind + payload schema + SQL migration landed in the commit that closes mod_proposed_entity_canvas_visibility (kind appended to packages/shared-types/src/events.ts; payload schema in packages/shared-types/src/events/proposals.ts; migration at apps/server/migrations/0012_session_events_entity_removed.sql; projector handler in apps/server/src/projection/replay.ts). The WS handler that consumes `withdraw-proposal` from the wire, validates proposer-only authority (rejection `'not-proposer'` mapped to wire 403), checks the proposal is still `'proposed'`, and emits one `entity-removed` per propose-time-created entity + `proposal-withdrawn` ack is unimplemented. This task lands the handler at apps/server/src/ws/handlers/withdraw.ts mirroring the propose / commit / vote skeleton plus the Cucumber wire-path coverage at tests/behavior/backend/ws-withdraw.feature.

        Surfaced via tech-debt registration policy in ORCHESTRATOR.md (commit landing mod_proposed_entity_canvas_visibility).
      ->8-
    }
    task facet_status_server_decompose_component_facets "Server-side symmetric arm: derive per-component classification:'proposed' facets for pending decompose / interpretive-split in apps/server/src/projection/facet-status.ts" {
      effort 1d
      allocate team
      complete 100
      depends !ws_proposal_status_broadcast
      note -8<-
        Source of debt: tasks/refinements/moderator-ui/mod_decompose_propose_time_canvas_visibility.md D5 + facetStatus.ts moderator-only mirror — the per-component `classification: 'proposed'` derivation for pending decompose / interpretive-split currently lives on the moderator client side only (apps/moderator/src/graph/facetStatus.ts walks the decompose / interpretive-split proposal payload and synthesizes per-component facet rows in `proposed` state during the proposed window). The server-side proposal-status broadcast emitter at apps/server/src/projection/facet-status.ts does NOT carry the symmetric arm — it derives facets from committed events only — so any non-moderator surface (participant_ui / audience) that consumes the `proposal-status` broadcast for facet styling will under-report the component facets until this arm lands. Closing this task grows the server-side walk-the-decompose-payload arm so client- and server-side derivations stay in lockstep beyond v1, and removes the moderator-only special-case from the client. Logical prerequisite (not encoded as depends to avoid the backend → moderator_ui cycle): moderator_ui.mod_graph_rendering.mod_decompose_propose_time_canvas_visibility — the propose-time fan-out this task mirrors lands there (commit landing mod_decompose_propose_time_canvas_visibility).
        Surfaced via tech-debt registration policy in ORCHESTRATOR.md (commit landing mod_decompose_propose_time_canvas_visibility).
      ->8-
    }
    task ws_label_snapshot_message "Label-snapshot write-side WS handler (C→S label-snapshot, S→C snapshot-labeled)" {
      effort 0.5d
      allocate team
      complete 100
      depends !ws_message_envelope, !ws_snapshot_message, data_and_methodology.methodology_engine.snapshot_create_logic
      note -8<-
        Source of debt: tasks/refinements/moderator-ui/mod_snapshot_label_input.md Decision §1.a — the label-snapshot write-side WS envelope (C→S `label-snapshot`, S→C `snapshot-labeled`) is a prerequisite for the snapshot label input modal. Mirrors the ws_commit_message / ws_meta_disagreement_message skeleton: subscribe-before-act gate, moderator-only authority gate (`'moderator-only'` rejection), `expectedSequence` optimistic-concurrency gate (`'sequence-conflict'`), call-through to snapshot_create_logic, append `snapshot-created` event, broadcast `event-applied`, ack with `snapshot-labeled` payload `{ snapshotId }`. Extends `wsMessageTypes` in packages/shared-types/src/ws-envelope.ts with `'label-snapshot'` (Group-B) and `'snapshot-labeled'` (Group-C) plus matching payload schemas and `WsMessagePayloadMap` entries.
        Registered by closer (2026-05-31) while closing moderator_ui.mod_snapshot_flow.mod_snapshot_label_input.
      ->8-
    }
